# Benchmark artifacts: for the PILOT, results/{raw,scores,human} ARE committed.
# At 48 outputs the full chain of evidence (every model output, judge score, and
# human grade) belongs in the repo — it's the strongest auditability signal we
# have. (Pre-pilot these were gitignored; un-ignored per the results-commit
# policy — see BUILD_LOG 2026-07-11.) If the suite ever scales past a few hundred
# records, revisit committing raw/.

# On-disk model response cache is a MECHANISM, not evidence — stays ignored.
.cache/
cache/

